bawden on Jun 10, 2024
I'm not sure how to correctly describe the KLH10, but I think calling it "the first PDP-10 emulator to run ITS", while true, is a bit of a misrepresentation of what KLH set out to do. If I recall correctly, Ken was developing the KLH10 because he had a customer who wanted to continue to run some PDP10 software, but wanted to ditch their DEC equipment. That customer was surely not running ITS, and was probably not using a KS10. A KS10 with ITS paging was just Ken's first step. Why Ken's customer couldn't use Grossman's emulator, I don't know, but it surely wasn't because it didn't run ITS!


